The paper discusses recent advances in unsupervised feature learning and deep learning, which are primarily focused on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also covers advances in manifold learning and computer vision (cs.CV), as well as probabilistic models and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the geometrical connections between representation learning, density estimation, and manifold learning, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
